he neology of the late Enlightenment and pointed not only back to conservative traditions but also forward to the Christology of more modern times.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 7aRELIGION / Christian Theology / General.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978077357141940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780773571419423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780773571419/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles